@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@{b}@{u}Required:@{ub}@{uu}

 * AmigaOS 2.04 (V36).
 * @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0} V3.0.
 * 1MB of free memory.
 * Parallelport sampler.
 * 200 KB of disk-space.

@{b}@{u}Highly recommended:@{ub}@{uu}

 * mc 68020 or better.
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"
 @{b}@{u}Features of Perfect Pitch:@{ub}@{uu}

 * @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0} gui with bubble- and online amigaguide help.
 * Bandwidth of 7 octaves (from 16.35 to 1975.53 Hz)
 * Full user configurable tuning tones.
 * @{"Funtion plotter" link "Function plotter" 0} for tuning tone generating with functions.
 * User-defined frequencies outside nominal notes.
 * All drawing pens customizable with @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0} Poppen class.
 * Three different @{"meters" link "Meters" 0}:
   - @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0} levelmeter-style frequency difference meter.
   - Hertz difference.
   - Percentage difference.
 * @{"Fast scope" link "Fast scope" 0} display for very fine tuning.
 * @{"Slower scope" link "Slower scope" 0} with lenght of 8 cycles for coarse tuning.
 * @{"List" link "List" 0} for guitar string as an example.
 * Very accurate (for technically interested persons: Audio
   channels are used for interrupts and modulating the interrupt
   frequency).
 * Localization.


What's new from version 1.1:

 * Localization.
 * Numerous bug fixes.
 * Bandwidth of 7 octaves (was 6 before).
@endnode

